Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.56,0:00:03.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnArial Black\pos(316,325)\fad(400,0)}Obey the Rules and manners\Nto have a fun Duel!!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.09,0:00:07.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Memory has been\N sealed away somehow!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.76,0:00:10.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even the God Cards\Nhave been stolen!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.49,0:00:14.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And... a new enemy has\N appeared before us.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.27,0:00:15.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Musketeers of Doma!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.20,0:00:20.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Using a Power of Darkness\N different from the Millennium Items,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.20,0:00:22.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}these people calling themselves\N "musketeers" challenge me to a Duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.47,0:00:23.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"Orichalcos"...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.94,0:00:28.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Is that power strong enough\N to control Obelisk?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.27,0:00:49.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sometime ago, for the sake of living, we left behind our happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.11,0:00:56.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We deceived ourselves, clinging to this mere illusion as we danced...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.61,0:01:02.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}With closed eyes, at the end of the horizon,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.87,0:01:08.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I was searching for your smiling face...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.29,0:01:16.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We embrace our dreams and continue on...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.22,0:01:23.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}within the swaying traces of memories...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.18,0:01:29.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Someday, I will once again grasp hold of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.31,0:01:36.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}these feelings I have locked away in my heart... Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.05,0:02:00.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Barrier of Orichalcos"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.86,0:02:29.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A barrier that imprisons even the gods?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.04,0:02:33.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even be thou hast Magnet Valkyrian,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.64,0:02:36.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ye shall be unable\N to beat a {\i1}God Card{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.47,0:02:38.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dark Obelisk, attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.22,0:02:43.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be gone! Magnet Valkyrian!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.15,0:02:45.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God Hand Crusher!!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.26,0:02:53.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.96,0:02:57.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't there a way\N to beat the powered-up Obelisk?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.70,0:03:00.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now your key card is gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.70,0:03:02.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll end my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.97,0:03:08.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Is this guy bent on using a God Card,\N knowing full well the risks entailed?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.95,0:03:25.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if we have the power\N of the Barrier of Orichalcos,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.06,0:03:28.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's impossible to completely\N control the gods, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.26,0:03:30.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps he isn't cut out\N to be a musketeer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.81,0:03:35.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's the best opponent to test the Nameless Pharaoh's power.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.52,0:03:39.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I have nothing to fight against\N a god with what I have now...!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.87,0:03:41.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.31,0:03:43.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll activate a Magic Card!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.14,0:03:45.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Angel's Charity!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.55,0:03:56.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With the effect of this card,\NI can draw three more cards
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.19,0:03:58.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and discard two cards\Nto the Graveyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.86,0:03:59.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And the next...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.16,0:04:04.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll Summon a Monster in Defense Mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.40,0:04:07.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, set one card.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.07,0:04:09.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn is complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.37,0:04:13.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.24,0:04:16.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set one card on the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.87,0:04:19.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dark Obelisk, attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.88,0:04:22.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God Hand Crusher!!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.82,0:04:26.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.88,0:04:30.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi just lost another Monster...!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.29,0:04:33.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It shall happen very soon...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.62,0:04:36.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It shall happen very soon, Sir Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.75,0:04:41.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thou shalt his soul\N be offered up to our god!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.09,0:04:43.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Offered?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.01,0:04:44.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.24,0:04:47.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The soul of the loser shall be offered up to God as a sacrifice!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.57,0:04:50.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Says he, this world shall be guided down the path of destruction!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.64,0:04:53.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be it food to a new, {\i1}pure{\i0} world!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.98,0:04:56.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is that guy saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.31,0:04:59.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know we've heard something like that before...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.94,0:05:04.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The omen has begun~
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.03,0:05:07.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Soon this world's gonna be destroyed~
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.20,0:05:11.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me! Did you do anything\Nto Haga and Ryuzaki?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.04,0:05:12.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly that!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.37,0:05:16.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.77,0:05:19.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you were up {\i1}there{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.27,0:05:20.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait right there!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.01,0:05:26.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay, Jounouchi?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.51,0:05:28.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Honda! You tryin' to kill me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.11,0:05:32.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Their souls are\N in our hands at the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.85,0:05:36.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They are the offerings\Nfor the Ancient God's revival.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.94,0:05:39.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Haga... Ryuzaki...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.06,0:05:40.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You sealed their souls in cards...?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.44,0:05:48.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Do they hold the same\N Power of Darkness Pegasus had?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.47,0:05:54.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I was gonna die...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.31,0:05:57.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go on. Be it thine turn, Sir Yugi.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.44,0:06:00.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If thy does not\N play a Monster Card this turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.31,0:06:02.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,thine soul shall \Nforever perish from this world!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.15,0:06:05.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.55,0:06:08.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Before you worry about {\i1}my{\i0} end...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.95,0:06:11.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...you'd better worry about {\i1}yourself{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.82,0:06:12.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you just say?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.19,0:06:16.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Magic Card,\N Resurrection of the Dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.90,0:06:19.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Monster I'll revive is...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.80,0:06:21.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Magnet Valkyrian!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.63,0:06:24.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's hopeless, hopeless!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.23,0:06:29.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Magnet Valkyrian does not hold enough\N Attack Power to defeat Dark Obelisk!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.47,0:06:32.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that Dark Obelisk\N has absolute power.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.18,0:06:35.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if you hold a strength\N that {\i1}surpasses{\i0} that power...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.28,0:06:38.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Power superior to Dark Obelisk?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.85,0:06:39.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.05,0:06:42.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The united power of {\i1}courage{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.25,0:06:43.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll show you right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.09,0:06:47.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I deactivate the combination\Nof Magnet Valkyrian!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.93,0:06:58.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next I activate\N a Magic Card from my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.44,0:07:00.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brave Attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.74,0:07:01.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.64,0:07:03.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Magnet Warriors!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.58,0:07:09.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.59,0:07:16.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What an utterly foolish move.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.39,0:07:17.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Art thou maniacle?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.33,0:07:19.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's {\i1}find out{\i0}, shall we?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.26,0:07:22.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look carefully at Dark Obelisk's body!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.36,0:07:25.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Madness!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.36,0:07:30.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Magnet Warriors' Attack Points\N should be inferior to Dark Obelisk's!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.40,0:07:35.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activated Brave Attack, which throws aside all fear and doubt,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.39,0:07:37.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,combining the strength of my Monsters...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.71,0:07:40.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...in order to fight against\N the opposing Monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.01,0:07:41.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.95,0:07:42.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.98,0:07:45.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alpha's Attack Power is 1400.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.69,0:07:48.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And Beta has 1700 Attack Points.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.52,0:07:52.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Obelisk has 3100 points of damage!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.86,0:07:56.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And Dark Obelisk's Attack Power is 4500.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.59,0:08:01.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When it takes, lastly, Magnet Warrior Gamma's\N 1500 Attack Points,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.75,0:08:02.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,what do you think will happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.57,0:08:06.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Magnet Warrior Gamma!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.12,0:08:23.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.85,0:08:24.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.96,0:08:27.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He defeated Dark Obelisk!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.22,0:08:28.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.86,0:08:30.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As expected of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.19,0:08:33.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think he's learned\N how to defeat the God Cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.50,0:08:34.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.20,0:08:37.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.10,0:08:40.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,True it be that Obelisk has disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.54,0:08:44.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, the Barrier of Orichalcos's power\N has only just shown itself!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.84,0:08:46.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Magic Card!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.58,0:08:47.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Treasure From Heaven!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.48,0:08:53.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now both sides\N have six cards in their hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.08,0:08:55.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Their Life Points are equal.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.29,0:08:59.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But every Monster he plays\N instantly gets powered up!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.59,0:09:02.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it's not like\N Yugi's disadvantage has changed...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.63,0:09:09.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.20,0:09:12.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When this guy is added to my hand\N by way other than a regular draw,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.07,0:09:14.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,at the moment I get the card
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.10,0:09:16.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can Summon the Monster to the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.44,0:09:19.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What can you do with a weakling like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.64,0:09:22.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll Summon Warrior Dai Grepher.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.42,0:09:32.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reverse card, open!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.26,0:09:34.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reviving Coffin of Black Magic!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.23,0:09:42.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When the opponent Summons a Monster, this card is able to revive a Magician-Type Monster in the Graveyard
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.70,0:09:46.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,after sacrificing Monsters\Nfrom both sides.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.04,0:09:55.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the one I'm going to bring back...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.21,0:09:56.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...is the Black Magician!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.35,0:10:03.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you used Angel's Charity
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.12,0:10:06.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you put Black Magician\Nin the Graveyard?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.29,0:10:07.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.12,0:10:09.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now you have no Monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.93,0:10:14.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On my next turn, I'll give you a fatal blow\N with my Black Magician!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.47,0:10:18.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll set a card and end my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.68,0:10:20.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.84,0:10:22.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I'm sure Yugi will win!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.04,0:10:24.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.74,0:10:26.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.58,0:10:28.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Black Magician!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.18,0:10:30.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Direct Attack him!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.18,0:10:32.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quickplay Magic, Shield Wall!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.08,0:10:34.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.05,0:10:37.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You think too little.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.32,0:10:42.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shield Wall is able to Summon four\N 1000 Defense Point Wall Monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.53,0:10:45.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thee attack won't even {\i1}touch{\i0} me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.03,0:10:49.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Yugi...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.27,0:10:54.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The real power of the Orichalcos Barrier\N has just been used!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.71,0:10:58.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Magic card, Bronze Knights, activate!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.68,0:11:04.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This card Summons Bronze Knight Tokens\N for each card I discard from my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.42,0:11:08.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.42,0:11:10.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are six Monsters!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.79,0:11:14.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-H-Hey! Hold on a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.49,0:11:16.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.39,0:11:20.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In Duel Monsters, you can only\N Summon up to five at a time!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.43,0:11:23.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.50,0:11:26.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Within The Barrier of Orichalcos, that is!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.34,0:11:33.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This barrier extends the Monster Spaces\N into your Magic and Trap Zones!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.21,0:11:34.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.61,0:11:39.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That means he can Summon\N up to {\i1}ten{\i0} Monsters on the field?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.48,0:11:40.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.35,0:11:43.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if the fore-running Monsters\N are not destroyed,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.29,0:11:46.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you can't attack the Monsters\Nin the back!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.16,0:11:46.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.12,0:11:50.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Use the power of Orichalcos\N and power up!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.46,0:11:52.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My Bronze Knights!!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.00,0:12:00.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Six Monsters...!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.97,0:12:03.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Against this many enemies, even with\N the Black Magician on my side, it's too much...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.70,0:12:08.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Plus, even if I were to use all my Attack Position Monsters to attack him at once,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.95,0:12:11.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}he would still be guarded by the back line of Defense Monsters...!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.22,0:12:14.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Barrier of Orichalcos...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.45,0:12:18.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This card has abilities\N like none I've ever seen...!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.09,0:12:20.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Seems like this'll be a tough fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.31,0:12:43.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set two cards face-down!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.61,0:12:47.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll then Summon Queen's Knight\N in Defense Position!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.25,0:12:48.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn is over!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.82,0:12:50.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.45,0:12:52.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Trap Card, activate!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.26,0:12:52.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.12,0:12:55.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dust Tornado!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.23,0:13:00.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This card is able to destroy one of \Nthe opponent's Magic or Trap Cards!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.10,0:13:04.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I destroy the Orichalcos Barrier!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.54,0:13:09.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.11,0:13:10.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you can just get rid of that barrier...!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.91,0:13:18.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.82,0:13:20.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Seal didn't disappear!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.45,0:13:21.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Futile effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.82,0:13:25.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Barrier of Orichalcos is protected by\N the great Power of the Orichalcos.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.62,0:13:28.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You won't be able to destroy it like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.16,0:13:29.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a pity.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.73,0:13:33.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll use the Magic Card, The Warrior Returning Alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.60,0:13:35.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll return Dai Grepher from\N the Graveyard to my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.97,0:13:37.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, Summon it to the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.74,0:13:41.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Absorb the power of the Orichalcos!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.00,0:13:42.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dai Grepher!!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.68,0:13:52.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll activate the Continuous Magic,\N The Allied Forces!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.02,0:13:57.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This card is able to enhance the Attack Power\N of every Warrior
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.15,0:13:59.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,by 200 points for every Warrior \Nand Spellcaster face-up on the field!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.62,0:14:01.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are four Warriors on the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.56,0:14:06.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thus, my Monsters\Nwill gain 800 points!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.50,0:14:08.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be gone! Black Magician!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.83,0:14:10.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dai Grepher, attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.60,0:14:17.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My attack isn't over!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.44,0:14:20.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now your other Monster\N will be killed as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.44,0:14:22.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sacrifice Escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.01,0:14:23.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.18,0:14:27.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quickplay Magic, Magical Academy!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.76,0:14:33.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Black Magician Girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.36,0:14:36.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After the player\Ndiscards 2 cards from their hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.02,0:14:39.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,this card will Summon a Monster of your choice,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.94,0:14:42.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,while adding two levels and\N 500 Attack Points to that Monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.93,0:14:47.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To think you'd offer your Monsters\N to add Attack Points to another...!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.47,0:14:50.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And depending on the number\Nof Black Magicians resting in the Graveyard,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.97,0:14:53.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she can gain 300 Attack Points!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.81,0:14:54.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.45,0:14:58.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He has seven Monsters\N on his side of the field...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.52,0:15:00.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There's no other way\Nto overturn the situation...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.05,0:15:02.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...than to draw that card.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.92,0:15:04.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If I don't draw it...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.46,0:15:07.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But I believe in my deck!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.93,0:15:10.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.40,0:15:15.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,YES!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.37,0:15:18.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Magic Card!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.31,0:15:21.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Diffusion Wave-Motion, activate!!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.40,0:15:22.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.34,0:15:25.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He drew Diffusion Wave-Motion\N in such timing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.71,0:15:32.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Black Magician Girl!!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.99,0:15:37.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Black Burning Burst!!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.62,0:15:43.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By paying 1000 of my Life Points,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.33,0:15:47.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Diffusion Wave-Motion allows me to\N attack every Monster on the field!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.40,0:15:48.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.03,0:15:52.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.41,0:15:56.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a close call.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.77,0:16:00.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Master... Ra...fa...el!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.81,0:16:03.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Th-The God Card...!!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.19,0:16:19.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gurimo...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.00,0:16:23.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he had just one more turn,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.67,0:16:25.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gurimo would have won.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.27,0:16:29.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not that interesting any more...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.01,0:16:30.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, let's retreat.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.77,0:16:31.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.30,0:16:34.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give the God cards back to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.58,0:16:37.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have to defeat\N all {\i1}three{\i0} of us {\i1}first{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.05,0:16:41.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someday I'll come back\Nto claim your soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.18,0:16:44.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah yes, I'll leave these weaklings to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.13,0:16:53.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.67,0:16:57.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Until we meet again.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.73,0:16:59.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nameless Pharaoh.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.40,0:17:00.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Wait a sec!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.57,0:17:02.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You wanna run away, cowards?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.07,0:17:05.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come down and fight us!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.58,0:17:09.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No rush, Katsuya Jounouchi.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.95,0:17:13.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll fight you guys soon enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.65,0:17:15.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Varon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.55,0:17:16.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Remember it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.15,0:17:18.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Stop right there!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.96,0:17:19.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.23,0:17:25.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is he dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.66,0:17:26.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.70,0:17:29.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But his soul is gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.27,0:17:32.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.74,0:17:36.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His soul is sealed in the Barrier's card.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.11,0:17:37.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.08,0:17:39.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.88,0:17:41.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.68,0:17:43.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.18,0:17:49.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This feeling resembles that of the Power of Darkness and the Millennium Items.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.63,0:17:58.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing all of a sudden?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.36,0:18:00.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! I'm gettin' the creeps here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.36,0:18:02.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's our line.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.50,0:18:04.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How can you run away\Nafter seeing us?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.83,0:18:06.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let them go.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.47,0:18:08.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jounouchi-{\i1}kun{\i0}, Honda-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.51,0:18:12.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanna ask you\Nwhat happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.61,0:18:15.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't remember a word of what\N you're talkin' about here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.15,0:18:16.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For real!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.61,0:18:20.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Are ye Sir Dinosaur Ryuzaki and Sir Insector Haga?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.28,0:18:22.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}W-What the hell...?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.66,0:18:24.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Do ya want somethin' wit' us?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.45,0:18:25.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Words are pointless!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.41,0:18:27.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}DUEL!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.86,0:18:32.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So we fought 'im after he\N challenged us to a Duel,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.03,0:18:33.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and got our butts handed to us!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.71,0:18:34.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.56,0:18:36.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We had a tough fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.43,0:18:41.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he used a wicked card,\N some kinda barrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.17,0:18:43.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Barrier of Orichalcos!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.21,0:18:44.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.84,0:18:45.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.58,0:18:47.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You one a' them?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.88,0:18:49.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How's that possible?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.65,0:18:53.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi got your souls back\Nfrom him!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.72,0:18:54.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.75,0:18:55.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That aside,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.02,0:18:59.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,what did you mean when you mentioned the omens of the end of the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.72,0:19:01.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did we say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.13,0:19:03.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't remember at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.99,0:19:04.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.99,0:19:05.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's not talk about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.06,0:19:09.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Yugi-{\i1}kun{\i0}, you have the\N God cards, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.53,0:19:11.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Won't you let me see them?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.84,0:19:13.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh yeah, yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.37,0:19:14.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About that...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.64,0:19:16.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They stole them...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.54,0:19:17.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say what?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.47,0:19:18.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you serious?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.71,0:19:19.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.91,0:19:23.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're gonna take em back from\N those jerks no matter what!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.25,0:19:24.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you remember anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.95,0:19:26.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,be sure to let us know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.02,0:19:26.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're counting on you guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.48,0:19:30.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be sure to!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.49,0:19:34.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.16,0:19:38.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We gotta be the ones to find em first!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.36,0:19:40.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-And get the God cards!\N -And get the God cards!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.97,0:19:45.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of which...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.37,0:19:48.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you guys heard the recent reports\Non TV or in papers...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.64,0:19:52.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The children's character is gone, like a body without a soul".
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.48,0:19:53.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.38,0:19:56.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But this seems to be happening\N all over the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.78,0:19:59.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps there are people\Nkilling the Duelists around the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.42,0:20:02.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Duelists that steal people's souls...?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.75,0:20:04.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hi, darling!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.39,0:20:07.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to see you, darling!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.79,0:20:10.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-Who are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.63,0:20:12.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, darling!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.40,0:20:16.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you forget about\Nour sweet promise?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.97,0:20:17.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.77,0:20:20.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! A {\i1}sweet promise{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.65,0:20:21.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come {\i1}on{\i0}~!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.49,0:20:25.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the card I got\N from my darling! It's {\i1}me{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.71,0:20:27.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Card?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.21,0:20:29.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This card...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.66,0:20:31.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Rebeca, take this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.25,0:20:34.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Bonds of Friendship?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.71,0:20:36.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I hope you'll accept it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.25,0:20:37.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.50,0:20:39.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.96,0:20:41.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rebeca!?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.49,0:20:42.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hi!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.23,0:20:45.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? You got a\N whole different look now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.96,0:20:48.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to\N that bear, "Teddy-{\i1}chan{\i0}"?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.26,0:20:50.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph! I outgrew stuff like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.97,0:20:54.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because I have a {\i1}real{\i0} boyfriend now~!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.57,0:20:57.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And just {\i1}who{\i0} is your boyfriend?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.54,0:21:00.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Americans sure are growing fast, Honda.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.68,0:21:03.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.28,0:21:05.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You came to Japan\Njust to meet Yugi?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.68,0:21:06.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yup!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.68,0:21:09.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's actually my grandfather\Nwho wants to talk to him!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.72,0:21:11.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Professor Hopkins does?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.99,0:21:17.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Professor Hopkins!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.33,0:21:20.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.83,0:21:23.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have something important to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.43,0:21:24.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi-{\i1}kun{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.60,0:21:27.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No... Nameless Pharaoh.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.14,0:22:02.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The houses lined down the street drifting by being dyed red
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.48,0:22:10.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If I notice pain, it'll turn into happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.07,0:22:21.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Every time people wipe away tears, they understand bonds
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.17,0:22:31.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The warm strength that you gave me will change into kindness
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.59,0:22:40.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Overflowing feelings don't stop
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.85,0:22:50.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll live while I feel it, for me to be myself
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.70,0:22:59.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Healed by overflowing friendship
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.96,0:23:04.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Our fated encounter is a truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.46,0:23:14.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and someday we'll be able to understand each other
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.87,0:23:18.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(131,117)}"Preview"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.08,0:23:20.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rebeca's abrupt visit to see Yugi...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.08,0:23:21.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.75,0:23:25.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She called Yugi "darling".\NThat's really surprising!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.15,0:23:29.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And Professor Hopkins\Nis waiting for Yugi at the Museum.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.26,0:23:30.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,along with the truth of the incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.49,0:23:34.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the ruins under the ocean...\NWhat is the connection?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.46,0:23:37.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it's related somehow to the other\N Yugi and his lost memories?!
